- Imports should use the '@/' prefix.
- Types should be documented with JSDoc.
- Except when avoiding a circular import, imports should be at the top of the file.


## Import Examples

```ts
// Correct
// src/app/(tabs)/myScreen.tsx
import { db } from '@/db/client';
```

```ts
// Incorrect
// src/app/(tabs)/myScreen.tsx
import { db } from '../../db/client';
```


## Import examples

```ts
// good
import TrackPlayer from "react-native-track-player
```

```ts
// bad
const TrackPlayer = await require("react-native-track-player)
```